# Bid Monitor UI — Athens Bid Ready

Bid Monitor is the Chrome companion to Athens **Bid Management**. Keep its UI visually aligned with that feature — not the purple Athens Settings chrome, and not generic system-UI / blue extension skins.

## Source of truth

| What | Where |
|------|--------|
| Tokens & patterns | `Athens/src/app/features/bid-management/bid-management.css` (`--bm-*`) |
| Fonts | Figtree (body), Bricolage Grotesque (display), JetBrains Mono (IDs/meta) |
| Extension tokens | `Bid-Monitor/sidepanel/tokens.css` — import this; do not invent new palettes |

## Tokens (required)

Use CSS variables from `tokens.css`. Never hard-code slate/blue hex for chrome.

- Surfaces: `--bm-ink`, `--bm-panel`, `--bm-panel-solid`, `--bm-line`
- Brand: `--bm-ember` / `--bm-ember-soft` (primary CTAs), `--bm-teal` / `--bm-teal-glow` (links, Apply, active chips)
- Type: `--bm-body`, `--bm-display`, `--bm-mono`
- Radius: `--bm-radius-sm|md|lg|pill`
- Page atmosphere: `--bm-page-bg` (ember + teal wash — not flat gray)

## Patterns

- **Titles / company names**: `font-family: var(--bm-display)`, tight tracking
- **Eyebrow labels**: uppercase, `~0.65rem`, bold, `letter-spacing: 0.08–0.12em`, muted
- **Cards**: panel surface + `--bm-line` border, radius 12–16px; frosted panels OK
- **Primary CTA** (Submit / Sign in): ember gradient (see `.btn-primary`)
- **Apply / success-adjacent**: teal (`.btn-apply`)
- **Secondary**: panel-solid + line border
- **Chips**: pill radius; Pending = ember soft; In process = success soft; Submitted = teal glow; Skipped = muted
- **Segmented controls**: track + teal active fill (not blue)
- **Copy**: short operational labels (“Bid Ready”, “In process”, “Submit”, “Skip”) — match Athens Bid Management language

## Do not

- Purple / indigo product chrome (`#6c5ce7`) in Bid Monitor
- Default stacks (Inter, Roboto, Arial, system-only) as the primary UI font
- Flat single-color `#f1f5f9` / blue `#2563eb` extension look
- New one-off color systems in `panel.css` / `popup.css` without updating `tokens.css`

## When changing UI

1. Extend `tokens.css` if a new semantic color is needed
2. Restyle via existing classes / variables
3. Keep side panel and popup on the same token file
4. Prefer Athens Bid Management CSS as the visual reference when unsure
